```

## Install

Static plugins compile **into** the engine binary. To use this plugin in
Genesis-Core:

1. Clone Genesis-Core: `git clone https://github.com/dmercer290-byte/wayland-core`
2. Add this crate as a path dep in the workspace `Cargo.toml`:
   ```toml
   [workspace]
   members = [
       # ...existing members...
       "../{{project-name}}",
   ]
   ```
3. Add a runtime dep on this crate from `crates/wcore-agent/Cargo.toml` (so
   `inventory::submit!` actually links in):
   ```toml
   [dependencies]
   {{project-name}} = { path = "../../../{{project-name}}" }
   ```
4. Rebuild the engine: `cargo install --path crates/wcore-cli`

For **dynamic** (on-disk, no engine rebuild required) plugins, use the
`plugin-wasm` or `plugin-subprocess` template instead.

## Layout

- `src/lib.rs` — `Plugin` impl + `PluginFactory` + `inventory::submit!` slot.
- The manifest is embedded inline as a TOML string; edit the `[permissions]`
  and capability blocks to declare what your plugin needs.

## API version

This template depends on `wcore-plugin-api` via git tag `v0.6.5-genesis-base`
(`PLUGIN_API_VERSION = "1.0"`). The host rejects plugins whose
`plugin_api_version` does not match. When `wcore-plugin-api` is published to
crates.io, the dep will be converted to a plain version string.
